1. Launch an instance with ubuntu 64bit ami as the image.
2. ssh into the instance.
3. Create the stress cpu script on the instance and name it let say stress_cpu_employee1.sh.
4. sudo chmod +x stress_cpu_employee1.sh
5. sudo cp stress_cpu_employee1.sh /etc/init.d/
6. sudo update-rc.d stress_cpu_employee1.sh defaults
7. Stop the instance and make a snapshot of it.